{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"7195d477-e9f4-455b-8fe4-bd6623e28c5f","content":"Here's the recommended MSTest setup:\n\n## 1. Project file (`MyTests.csproj`) — minimal with MSTest.Sdk:\n\n```xml\n<Project Sdk=\"MSTest.Sdk/3.8.2\">\n\n  <PropertyGroup>\n    <TargetFramework>net8.0</TargetFramework>\n  </PropertyGroup>\n\n</Project>\n```\n\nThat's it — MSTest.Sdk handles all package references, `using` directives, and the MTP runner automatically.\n\n## 2. Enable parallel execution — add a `.runsettings` file:\n\n```xml\n<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"utf-8\"?>\n<RunSettings>\n  <MSTest>\n    <Parallelize>\n      <Workers>0</Workers>  <!-- 0 = use processor count -->\n      <Scope>ClassLevel</Scope>\n    </Parallelize>\n  </MSTest>\n</RunSettings>\n```\n\nOr use the assembly-level attribute in a file like `AssemblyInfo.cs`:\n\n```csharp\n[assembly: Parallelize(Scope = ExecutionScope.ClassLevel)]\n```\n\n## 3. Make database tests sequential — use `[DoNotParallelize]`:\n\n```csharp\n[TestClass]\n[DoNotParallelize]\npublic class DatabaseIntegrationTests\n{\n    [TestMethod]\n    public async Task InsertUser_WritesToDatabase()\n    {\n        // runs sequentially, never overlaps with other [DoNotParallelize] classes\n    }\n\n    [TestMethod]\n    public async Task DeleteUser_RemovesFromDatabase()\n    {\n        // also sequential\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n- `[DoNotParallelize]` on a class ensures its tests run sequentially and never concurrently with other non-parallel tests.\n- `Scope = ClassLevel` means tests *within* a class run sequentially, but different classes run in parallel — safest default.\n- Use `Scope = MethodLevel` if you want maximum parallelism (even methods within a class run concurrently).","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"05ce978c-6270-4e65-833e-b46d96cd54d4","outputTokens":496,"requestId":"E449:389F98:33BFD70:393F855:6A02FC08"},"id":"d080da43-7033-4d59-b715-a10c6647497c","timestamp":"2026-05-12T10:08:21.240Z","parentId":"b973bfe6-e0ea-4004-a58d-7d24597704b7"}
